<n-docbody><doc bill="Y"><content.metadata.block><cmd.identifiers><cmd.cites><cmd.second.line.cite><bop/><bos/>Multidistrict Lit Man § 3:16<eos/><eop/></cmd.second.line.cite></cmd.cites></cmd.identifiers></content.metadata.block><prop.block><prop.head toc-guid=""><bop/><bos/><headtext>Multidistrict Litigation Manual</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><content.metadata.block><cmd.dates><cmd.currency.default iso.d="20190501"><bop/><bos/>May 2019 Update<eos/><eop/></cmd.currency.default></cmd.dates></content.metadata.block><author.line><bop/><bos/><author>David F. Herr[<footnote.reference refid="If22f20b16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">a0</footnote.reference>]</author><eos/><eop/></author.line><prop.head toc-guid="I97b7f560933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Part</label.name><label.designator>I.</label.designator><headtext>Handling Cases Before the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head><prop.head toc-guid="I9f85f1c0933b11da99e2b07024dacc26"><bop/><bos/><label.name>Chapter</label.name><label.designator>3.</label.designator><headtext>Powers of the Panel</headtext><eos/><eop/></prop.head></prop.block><message.block><include.copyright n-include_collection="w_wlnv_msg" n-include_guid="I1DA35ED81DD211B281BAD200220BDFCA">Copyright (c) 2017 Thomson/RIA All rights reserved.</include.copyright></message.block><section><section.front><doc.title toc-guid="I94edd010e1e311da9c26e67ca3b71335"><head parent="doc.title"><bop/><bos/><label.name>§ </label.name><label.designator>3:16.</label.designator><headtext>Rulemaking power</headtext><eos/><eop/></head></doc.title></section.front><section.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>The Panel is also given by statute express authority to make rules governing procedure before the Panel.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If23080406b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">1</footnote.reference>] The Panel promulgated rules pursuant to its statutory authority early in its existence,[<footnote.reference refid="If230a7516b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">2</footnote.reference>] and has periodically revised those rules.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If230a7536b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">3</footnote.reference>] The rules were reorganized and renumbered and new rules were added as part of the 1988 amendments. <eos/><bos/>The rules were extensively revised in 2001, and again with revisions that took effect on October 4, 2010. <eos/><bos/>The current rules are set forth in <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs4:34" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If230ce606b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">Section 4:34</cite.query>.[<eos/><bos/><footnote.reference refid="If230ce616b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">4</footnote.reference>]</paratext><eos/><eop/></para></section.body></section><author.footnotes><footnote ID="If22f20b16b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>a0</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext>Maslon Edelman Borman &amp; Brand, LLP, Minneapolis, Minnesota.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote></author.footnotes><footnote.block><footnote ID="If23080406b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>1</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See</ital> <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-seq-number="00001" w-ref-type="LQ" w-normalized-cite="28USCAS1407" w-pub-number="1000546" ID="I54f9c4306b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">28 U.S.C.A. § 1407(f)</cite.query>. <eos/><bos/>The statute is reprinted in <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs3:19" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If230a7506b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">§ 3:19</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If230a7516b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>2</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See</ital> Panel Rules, <ital>reprinted in</ital> <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs4:34" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If230a7526b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">§ 4:34</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If230a7536b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>3</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See</ital> <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-serial-number="0292103006" w-seq-number="00002" w-ref-type="LR" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fb4ad16b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">50 F.R.D. 203 (1971)</cite.query>, <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-serial-number="0292103233" w-seq-number="00003" w-ref-type="LR" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fb4ad36b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">53 F.R.D. 119 (1972)</cite.query>, <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-serial-number="0292103243" w-seq-number="00004" w-ref-type="LR" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fb4ad56b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">65 F.R.D. 253 (1975)</cite.query>, <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-serial-number="0292127044" w-seq-number="00005" w-ref-type="LR" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fb4ad76b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">89 F.R.D. 273 (1981)</cite.query>; <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-serial-number="0292130929" w-seq-number="00006" w-ref-type="LR" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fb4ad96b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">199 F.R.D. 425 (2001)</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote><footnote ID="If230ce616b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2"><label.designator>4</label.designator><footnote.body><para><bop/><bos/><paratext><ital>See</ital> <cite.query w-src-number="0304913964" w-seq-number="00007" w-ref-type="RP" w-normalized-cite="268FRD436" w-pub-number="0000344" ID="I54fe09f16b3e11e9bfe8894985907fa8">Rules of Procedure of the Judicial Panel on Multidistrict Litigation, effective October 4, 2010, <ital>reprinted in</ital> 268 F.R.D. 436 (2010)</cite.query>. <eos/><bos/>The current Panel Rules are reprinted in their entirety in <cite.query w-ref-type="NA" w-normalized-cite="MDLITMANs4:34" w-pub-number="185218" ID="If230ce626b3e11e99b03e53d6dd36aa2">section 4:34</cite.query>.<eos/></paratext><eop/></para></footnote.body></footnote>